This paper discusses the use of SPARQL as a query language for Linked Data on the Web, which involves topics related to databases (cs.DB), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), deep learning (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper specifically focuses on the semantics and computability of SPARQL queries, which are relevant to all of these sub-categories. However, since the paper is primarily concerned with querying data on the Web, cs.DB and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
